  3.907738255398263*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2bc113ad-c449-442f-aec1-\
95408d0e0cc0"],

Cell["\<\
Four Nambu indices specify univocally each of the 16 Nambu components of the \
polarization propagator. Normal (anomalous) components possess an even (even \
or odd) number of \[OpenCurlyQuote]1\[CloseCurlyQuote] and \[OpenCurlyQuote]2\
\[CloseCurlyQuote] indices. In total, there are 6 normal (indices 1-6 of \
GPPNambu) and 10 anomalous components (indices 7-16 of GPPNambu) . Once \
\[OpenCurlyQuote]NppIdx\[CloseCurlyQuote] is specified, the Nambu component \
is fixed.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9077382215659647`*^9, {3.9077382923703613`*^9, 3.9077384065565405`*^9}, {
   3.9077384522680173`*^9, 3.9077384848449383`*^9}, {3.9077430709590244`*^9, 
   3.907743126073769*^9}, {3.9077450424291105`*^9, 3.9077450765315623`*^9}, {
   3.9228836915179586`*^9, 3.9228836938266754`*^9}, 
   3.9471617698109493`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"28028ffb-fb77-4f23-b4c3-\
e44a06338444"],

